This was the basis of my startup that went completely bust. Ran out of money for further development, and got dicked around by people who I formerly trusted for far too long. Still, I learned a ton from that experience. Like who to trust, not to trust, what advice is solid, and what advice is pure crap. In anycase, I figure documenting your failures so you learn from them, is far more important than successes. 

